HEADWORD: Picaroon
<hw>Pic`a*roon"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.
<ets>picaron</ets>, aug. of <ets>picaro</ets> roguish, n., a
rogue.]</ety> <def>One who plunders; especially, a plunderer of wrecks;
a pirate; a corsair; a marauder; a sharper.</def> <rj><au>Sir W.
Temple.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

